---
import BookLayout from '../layouts/BookLayout.astro';
import EmailReveal from '../components/EmailReveal.astro';
import { getSlugMap } from '../config/slug-resolver.js';

const _slugMap = getSlugMap();

function resolveWikilinks(text: string): string {
  return text
    .replace(/\[\[([^\]|]+)\|([^\]]+)\]\]/g, (_, s, lbl) => {
      const found = _slugMap[s];
      return `<a href="${found ? found.path : '/rules/' + s}">${lbl}</a>`;
    })
    .replace(/\[\[([^\]]+)\]\]/g, (_, s) => {
      const found = _slugMap[s];
      return `<a href="${found ? found.path : '/rules/' + s}">${found ? found.title : s}</a>`;
    });
}
---

<BookLayout title="Glass Empires SRD">
  <p>
    <strong>Glass Empires</strong> is a Braunstein-style tabletop RPG of faction politics,
    pre-industrial power, and civil warfare on the discworld of Aia. The island of Glass is burning. The immortal emperor has abdicated his throne, and all-out civil war is upon the land.
    <a href="https://glassempires.com">Learn more about the game →</a>
  </p>
  <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("While Glass Empires is mostly OSR-compatible & can be played as a traditional (if odd) D&D-like title, it is <emphasis>not</emphasis> a game about dungeon-crawling (not <emphasis>primarily</emphasis>, at least) & the gameplay loop bears little resemblance to the loops most typified by other RPGs. This is a game about [[sovereignty-subfactions|relationships]], [[debt-credit|debt]], [[what-is-a-faction|rulership,]] & [[divination|the nature of the divine]]. In a very real way, your faction is both <emphasis>synonymous with</emphasis> & <emphasis>more important than</emphasis> your character. It is a critical assumption that you are at the very least interested in a [[type-personality-cult|cult of personality]] as a great hero, and far more preferably, that you will <emphasis>rule an empire</emphasis> or <emphasis>die trying</emphasis>.")}>
  </p>
  <p>
    This is the System Reference Document, containing the complete rules, setting, and bestiary
    for Glass Empires and the faction engine powering it!
    Use the navigation on the left, or search by keyword using the button above.!
  </p>

  <p>
    Glass Empires is in open beta. Parts of the rules are still incomplete or in playtesting! Feedback is appreciated. Email: <EmailReveal />
  </p>

  <h2>At a glance</h2>

  <div class="qa-grid">

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>I want to run a game tonight.</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("[[creation-process|Character creation]] takes 10 minutes. The [[scenario|main scenario]] has pre-built high-level faction situations ready to drop into play. Start with a house war, a caravan in need of protection, or a village that stopped paying taxes.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>What do players actually do?</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("They lead a Party-as-[[what-is-a-faction|faction]]: recruit [[level-retainer|retainers]], negotiate with [[lord|lords]], hunt monsters for [[ritual-cooking|ritual cooking]], and escalate their faction's power. Every action is a [[moves|Move]] resolved against a 2d6 Save.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>How is this different from D<span class="amp-alt">&amp;</span>D?</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("No skill list. Your capabilities come from [[facts|Facts]], true statements about who your character is. Your [[level-retainer|Level]] comes from how many people follow you. Power flows through [[level-retainer|followers]], not murder or gold.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>What's with the cannibalism?</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("[[ritual-cooking|Ritual cooking]] is a component of the setting. Kill a creature, cook it, gain its strength ... and its nature. Want to fly? Eat a Qilin. Want superhuman strength? Eat a stronger human. Each meal is a gamble: power comes with the price of becoming what you consume.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>How do factions work?</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("Every PC leads a [[what-is-a-faction|Faction]] with a [[faction-types|type]] (Army, Business, Government, Mine Clan, Personality Cult, Godscult). Factions have resources & a Capital, and learning how to wield them is just as important as wielding your own sword.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>My friend wants to play a wizard.</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("[[magician|Magicians]] are spirit-speakers who capture spells as [[totems|Totems]]. Six [[magical-traditions|traditions]] (Jester, Origami Assassin, Forester, Metallurge, Snowmime, Telluric Priest) are available, each with unique mechanics. Magic is powerful, unstable, and demands respect. Most magicians die horribly.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>What's the setting?</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("[[island-of-glass|The island of Glass]] on the discworld of [[world-of-aia|Aia]]. THe immortal emperor abdicated. Three houses at war, a populist uprising, a salamander mineral cartel, and a passive-aggressive [[the-moon|Lunar Kingdom]] watching from above. Every faction has a goal. Every goal creates conflict.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="qa-card">
      <h3>How does combat work?</h3>
      <p set:html={resolveWikilinks("[[battle-rating|Battle Rating]] (BR) measures combat power at a glance. [[skirmishes|Skirmishes]] resolve personal fights with granular actions (Move, Strike, Cast, Disengage). [[battles|Battles]] handle any larger-scale combat without grids. [[damage-types|Damage]] comes in types with different effects.")}>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</BookLayout>

<style>
  .qa-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25em;
    margin: 1.5em 0;
  }
  .qa-card {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 0.35em;
    padding: 1.25em;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .qa-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5em;
  }
  .amp-alt {
    font-family: 'Literata Variable', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .qa-card p {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  @media (max-width: 48em) {
    .qa-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
